[h1 align=center] How to create your own Podweb page

[p-]
Podweb lets you publish your own little page inside Picotron using nothing
but a plain text file. Every Lexaloffle user already has podnet storage
tied to their account - just drop an index.podweb file there and you are live.
You can also host on the world wide web via https.
[-p]

[p] scared of using your podnet storage? There is more than you think! [download url=https://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/cposts/po/podnet_state-1.p64.png] to check
[break]
[p] Already know markdown? [link- file=markdown-to.podweb]click here[-link] We can handle that to... sort of.

[h2] A complete example

[p] This single file shows every tag in one go:

[code-]
[meta-]
domain: yourname.podweb
[-meta]

[font id=fancy url=podnet://78402/fonts/widesquat.font height=10]

[h1 align=center] Welcome to my page
[h2] A section
[h3] A sub section

[p] This is a short paragraph.

[p font=fancy] This is a paragraph in the above connected fancy font

[p-]
This is a longer paragraph that spans
multiple lines in the source file.
The browser joins them into one wrapped block.
It can also contain an [link- file=other.podweb]inline link[-link] right inside it.
[-p]

[break height=20]

[link file=other.podweb] A standalone link to another page

[img url=podnet://YOUR_ID/banner.gfx]

[download url=podnet://YOUR_ID/myfile.txt]

[link cart=sakura] Launch a Picotron cartridge
[-code]

[h2] Tag reference

[link file=how-to/meta.podweb] meta - page metadata and domain names
[link file=how-to/font.podweb] font - loading and using custom fonts
[link file=how-to/headings.podweb] headings - h1 h2 h3 with font and align
[link file=how-to/paragraph.podweb] paragraph - p blocks, inline links, inline downloads, align
[link file=how-to/link.podweb] link - standalone navigation links and cart links
[link file=how-to/image.podweb] image - img with align and resize
[link file=how-to/download.podweb] download - file download links
[link file=how-to/code.podweb] code - code blocks
[link file=how-to/break.podweb] break - vertical spacing
[link file=how-to/webring.podweb] webring - joining and creating webrings
[link file=how-to/publish.podweb] publish - getting your page live and sharing it
[link file=how-to/colors.podweb] colors - theming, per-element color and hover color
[link file=how-to/tipps-and-tricks.podweb] tips and tricks - coloured nav headers and more
[link file=how-to/change-start-page.podweb] change your start page - cli, create_process, bbs link, embedded iframe
[link file=how-to/comments.podweb] comments - adding a comment section to your page

